From: cmkuo@cs.utexas.edu (Chin-Ming Kuo)
Subject: Lucid emacs 19.8
Date: 2 Dec 1993 15:41:23 -0600


Lucid 19.8 on Linux

I've built the 19.8 vesion of Lucid emacs without much trouble.
The fixes are taken from 19.6, mixed with GNU emacs19.21's linux.h.

Compile with gcc -O2 shows that speed is quite good.
Font-locking a ~4k line C++ file takes 23 sec. vs. 18 sec. on
un-optimized lemacs on Sparc2. 

shell, ange-ftp, rmail all work fine. 
Since I'm only 1 week new to Linux, I would like some auditing on my
patches. if you're interested in the patches. Drop me a line.

-- 
C-M Kuo, guest @cs.utexas.edu

