W.R.Volz (hwrvo@usho42.hou281.chevron.com) wrote:
: Does anyone know when SLS will be released with  the new XFREE 2.0
: version? I want to upgrade my linux system, but want to wait until
: I can get that part as a package. Don't want to do too mush system
: tinkering, just want it to work. Complete reinstall is much faster
: than tinkering, since the last update I made was in March.

SLS seems to have been abondoned on the net.

1.04 was released on cd-rom a while back, but was
never uploaded to any ftp site. 1.03 is still
the newest version available.

If you are serious on upgrading, I suggest you use
the Slackware distribution. It is an outgrowth of a project
to fix SLS bugs and has now evolved into the premier disk-based
distribution.

The current slackware contains Xfree 2.0 and all the niceties 
required to make sure it runs.

enjoy!

--chuck

