From: sferris@budapest.math.macalstr.edu (Scott Ferris)
Subject: Re: Adaptec 2842 support?
Date: 2 Dec 1993 22:07:57 GMT

Ron Arts (raarts@hacktic.nl) wrote:
> Newsgroups: comp.os.linux.misc
> Subject: Adaptec 2842 support?    

> Does anybody know if AHA 2842 support will come?
> Is it being worked on?

  Does anyone know what chipset the 2842 uses?  I'll be working
on a driver for the 2742, but I haven't seen any specs for
the 2842, so I don't know if it also uses the same aic-7770 ASIC.
If it does, most of my code could be used.  You'd only
need to write a wrapper that initializes the 2842, as I only
have info on the EISA 274x series.  If it's the same ASIC
and I have time, I could try to write any needed 2842 code, though
I wouldn't be able to test it myself.  I've also heard of motherboards
that have the aic-7770 builtin.  If anyone has docs on how such
a motherboard addresses the ASIC I oculd try to get that working
as well.


